Ireland May Use Pension Levy to Fund Jobs Plan, Times Says

-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 
2011-04-24T10:33:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/ireland-may-use-pension-levy-to-fund-jobs-plan-times-says.html
Ireland may introduce a 500
million-euro stimulus plan next month to create jobs, funded by
a 0.5 percent levy on private pension funds, the  Sunday Times 
reported, citing unnamed government sources.  The government has said it does not intend to raise taxes
to fund a package, to be published in May, to create jobs.  To contact the reporter on this story:  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
